Workbench Usage
===============

    To start @{b}Ted@{ub} just double-click on its icon. @{b}Ted@{ub} supports multiple
icon selection on startup to automatically open the selected files.

    @{b}Ted@{ub} supports the following tooltypes:

@{b}STARTUP@{ub}
     ARexx script to execute on startup

@{b}PUBSCREEN@{ub}
     name of the public screen to use

@{b}FONTNAME@{ub}
     name of the font to use

@{b}FONTSIZE@{ub}
     height of the font to use

@{b}CX_POPKEY@{ub}
     hotkey to access the commodity

@{b}CX_PRIORITY@{ub}
     priority of the editor

@{b}ICONIFY@{ub}
     starts the editor in iconified mode


@EndNode

@Node "Ted Shell" "TDS.guide/Ted Shell"
@Next "Menu File"
@Prev "Ted Workbench"
@Toc "Ted"

Shell Usage
===========

    Usage: Ted FILE/M,PROJECT/K,STARTUP/K,PUBSCREEN/K

@{b}FILE/M@{ub}
     list of text files to load

@{b}PROJECT/K@{ub}
     project file to load

@{b}STARTUP/K@{ub}
     ARexx script to execute on startup

@{b}PUBSCREEN/K@{ub}
     name of the public screen to use

    There is also a little program called @{b}Ed@{ub} which acts as a frontend
to @{b}Ted@{ub}. @{b}Ed@{ub} will try to find a running version of the editor and open
the file on it, otherwise it will start a new copy of the editor.

    Usage: Ed FILE/M,PROJECT/K


