Menu Compile
============

    This menu contains the commands to compile source files, to build an
entire executable program and to run and debug it. All the commands use
the project file defined with the commands of the @{"Project" Link "Menu Project"} menu.

    The commands @{"Compile" Link "Compile-Compile"}, @{"Build" Link "Compile-Build"} and @{"Build All" Link "Compile-Build All"} are not built into the
editor, but their execution is demanded to @{b}TMake@{ub}. When one of these
commands has been selected, @{b}Ted@{ub} starts @{b}TMake@{ub} which executes the command
and if it finds some errors, returns an error list to @{b}Ted@{ub}. Using the
multitasking facilities of the operating system @{b}TMake@{ub} runs in
background, so you can continue to edit your source files. Also these
commands open a console window where it's possible to follow the
compiling process and to interrupt it with Ctrl-C. This feature can be
disabled with the @{b}No TMake Window@{ub} option of the @{"Options" Link "Project-Options"} requester.


