Project/Linker
--------------

    Opens the requester with the options for the linker:

@{b}Command@{ub}
     Command of the linker.
          e.g. "slink" (for SAS C)

@{b}Debug Opt.@{ub}
@{b}Final Opt.@{ub}
     @{b}Debug Opt.@{ub} are the options used if the @{b}Use Debug Options@{ub} is set in
     the @{"Options" Link "Project-Options"} requester, otherwise @{b}Final Opt.@{ub} will be used.

     The following strings have a special meaning:

    @{b}%obj@{ub}
          Names of the object files.

    @{b}%lnk@{ub}
          Name of the file containing the names of the object files.

    @{b}%lib@{ub}
          Names of the link libraries specified with the @{b}Libraries@{ub}
          gadget.

    @{b}%exe@{ub}
          Name of the executable file.

    @{b}%err@{ub}
          Name of the error file (if not present, then standard output
          will be used).

     e.g.
          @{b}FROM lib:c.o %obj TO %exe LIB %lib@{ub}
          where
          @{b}test.o@{ub} and @{b}sub.o@{ub} are the object files
          @{b}lib:lc.lib@{ub} and @{b}lib:amiga.lib@{ub} are the libraries
          @{b}test@{ub} is the executable file
          becomes
          @{b}FROM lib:c.o test.o sub.o TO test LIB lib:lc.lib lib:amiga.lib@{ub}

@{b}Object Ext.@{ub}
     File extension of the object files.

@{b}Libraries@{ub}
     List of link libraries. Use the @{b}Add@{ub}, @{b}Delete@{ub}, @{b}+@{ub}, @{b}-@{ub} buttons to add,
     delete and reorder the libraries files.


