          Name of the current source file.

    @{b}%mod@{ub}
          Name of the current source file without extension.

    @{b}%base@{ub}
          Name of the current source file without extension and path.

    @{b}%screen@{ub}
          Name of the public screen used by the editor.

     These options are very useful if you use the Amiga-E or TeX
     compilers.  Therefore you can have more than one source file per
     project and run or display only the current one (see the example
     project files).

@{b}Window@{ub}
