Settings/Create Icons?
----------------------

    If set, @{b}Ted@{ub} will create an icon for every file saved. Moreover it
uses the @{b}.info@{ub} files to store the position and size of the window and
the last position of the cursor. The @{b}.info@{ub} file used depends on the
extension of the file to be saved. @{b}Ted@{ub} will try to use a file called
@{b}ENV:TDS/def_XXX.info@{ub} or @{b}ENV:SYS/def_XXX.info@{ub} where XXX is the extension
of the file. So if you save a file called @{b}mydoc.txt@{ub} which doesn't have
an icon, @{b}Ted@{ub} will try to add an @{b}.info@{ub} file called @{b}ENV:TDS/def_TXT.info@{ub}
or @{b}ENV:SYS/def_TXT.info@{ub}. The are already some icon files in the @{b}ENV:TDS@{ub}
directory, but you can add your own files or change the existing one if
you don't like them.


@EndNode

