Settings/Editor
---------------

    Opens a requester with the options for the editor:

@{b}Requester@{ub}
     Defines the type of requester to use: @{b}ASL@{ub} or @{b}ReqTools@{ub}.  If the
     @{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is not installed, then it will always use the
     @{b}asl.library@{ub}.

@{b}Select Mode@{ub}
     Defines how the mouse button should be used to mark blocks. There
     are 2 options: @{b}Single Click@{ub} and @{b}Double Click@{ub}.

@{b}Tabwidth@{ub}
     Sets the width of the tab.

@{b}Left Margin@{ub}
@{b}Right Margin@{ub}
     Sets the left and right margin (used by @{"WordWrap" Link "Settings-WordWrap"} and @{"Format" Link "Edit-Format"}).

@{b}Max. Changes@{ub}
     Sets the maximum number of changes recorded for every file.

@{b}Autosave Delay@{ub}
     Sets the time for the autosave mode in minutes.

@{b}Priority@{ub}
     Sets the priority of the editor.

@{b}AutoIndent@{ub}
     Activates the automatic indentation.

@{b}WordWrap@{ub}
     Activates the automatic wordwrap at the end of a line.

@{b}OverStrike@{ub}
     Activates the overstrike mode.

@{b}WrapCursor@{ub}
     Defines the behaviour of the cursor at the end of the line. If set,
     then the cursor will go to the start of the next line, otherwise it
     will continue to move to the right on the same line.

@{b}Stripblanks@{ub}
     Removes any blanks and tabs from the end of the line which has
     been modified.

@{b}Autosave@{ub}
     Activates the autosave mode.

@{b}Create Icons@{ub}
     See @{"Settings-Create Icons?" Link "Settings-Create Icons?"}.

@{b}Ask Before Quit@{ub}
     If set, a requester will appear before the last window will be
     closed to inform the user that the program will be quit.

@{b}Backup@{ub}
     Creates a backup file called @{b}#?.bak@{ub} in the directory specified
     with @{b}Backup Dir@{ub} for every file saved.

@{b}Backup Dir@{ub}
     Sets the directory to use for backups. If no directory is specified
     then the backup file will be created in the same directory of the
     original file. Using a directory on the same volume of the original
     file is faster than using one on a different volume. In the first
     case the program has only to rename the file, whereas in the
     second case it has to copy the file.

@{b}Guide@{ub}
     Defines the guide to use for the on-line help.

@{b}Hotkey@{ub}
     Defines the hotkey used to deiconify @{b}Ted@{ub}.


@EndNode

