Twilight Make (TMake)
*********************

    @{b}TMake@{ub} is similar to the program @{b}make@{ub} used in the development of
programs composed of more than one source file. It checks every source
file if it has been modified and depending on the file extension (e.g.
@{b}.c@{ub} or @{b}.asm@{ub}) compiles or assembles it. Then it links all the object
files together to obtain the executable file. @{b}TMake@{ub} doesn't use
@{b}makefiles@{ub}, but instead relies on project files created with @{b}Ted@{ub}.

    It has been designed to interface to the most popular compilers like
SAS C, Lattice C, Aztec C, DICE C, PCQ, GNU-C, Oberon, and assemblers
like DevPac, A68k and even programs like TeX, CatComp and MakeInfo.
It's also possible to write a custom message converter if the compiler
used is not supported. @{b}TMake@{ub} can also be used as a standalone program
from Shell or Workbench to build projects created with @{b}Ted@{ub}.

    Usage: TMake PROJECT,FILE/K,ALL/S,PORTNAME/K,PRI=PRIORITY/K/N

@{b}PROJECT@{ub}
     name of the project file

@{b}FILE/K@{ub}
     if given, compiles only a single file

@{b}ALL@{ub}
     compiles all files, even if they have not been modified

@{b}PORTNAME@{ub}
     option used by @{b}Ted@{ub} to set the name of the message port used by
     @{b}TMake@{ub}

@{b}PRIORITY@{ub}
     priority of @{b}TMake@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "TRefs" "TDS.guide/TRefs"
@Next "Special Thanks"
@Prev "TMake"
@Toc "Main"

Twilight Reference Generator (TRefs)
************************************

    @{b}TRefs@{ub} generates reference files used by the @{"Find Reference" Link "Search-Find Reference"} command.
With this command it's possible to get information about a particular
keyword, e.g. moving the cursor to the word @{b}Window@{ub} and selecting the
@{"Find Reference" Link "Search-Find Reference"} command will result in the loading of the file
@{b}intuition.h@{ub} and the editor positioning the cursor to the start of the
definition of the structure @{b}struct Window@{ub}. Currently @{b}TRefs@{ub} can be used
to generate reference files from include files @{b}#?.h@{ub}, autodocs files
@{b}#?.doc@{ub} and AmigaGuide files @{b}#?.guide@{ub}.

    Usage: TRefs REFS/K/A,FILES/M/A

@{b}REFS/K/A@{ub}
     name of reference file to create

@{b}FILES/M/A@{ub}
     list of files to search

Here comes the format of the reference files for anybody who wants to
make his own reference generator:

     [file]
     keyword1=row1
     keyword2=row2
     ...

Using @{b}TRefs@{ub} with the file @{b}intuition.h@{ub} generates the following reference
file:

     [intuition/intuition.h]
     Menu=61
     MenuItem=89
     ...
     TabletHookData=1661
     [intuition/intuitionbase.h]
     IntuitionBase=66
     [intuition/preferences.h]
     Preferences=58
     [intuition/screens.h]
     DrawInfo=66
     Screen=133
     NewScreen=462
     ...


@EndNode

